  <text>
    <body>
      <div type="page" n="120">
        <pb n="120"/>
        <lg xml:id="block_A" xml:lang="he" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F6c4bac16-639d-4efb-80fc-190ead3118e5.jp2/1272,471,2023,699/max/0/default.jpg">
          <l>קַבָּלַת פָּנִים</l>
          <l>KABBALAT PANIM WELCOMING</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:id="block_B" xml:lang="he" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F6c4bac16-639d-4efb-80fc-190ead3118e5.jp2/2866,1829,1223,941/max/0/default.jpg">
          <l>בָּרוּךְ אַתָּה, יְיָ</l>
          <l>אֱלֹהֵינוּ, מֶלֶךְ הָעוֹלָם,</l>
          <l>אֲשֶׁר קִדְּשָׁנוּ בְּמִצְוֹתָיו,</l>
          <l>וְצִוָּנוּ לְהַדְלִיק</l>
          <l>נֵר שֶׁל שַׁבָּת.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:id="block_C" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F6c4bac16-639d-4efb-80fc-190ead3118e5.jp2/406,1871,1087,908/max/0/default.jpg">
          <l>BARUCH atah, Adonai</l>
          <l>Eloheinu, Melech haolam,</l>
          <l>asher kid&apos;shanu b&apos;mitzvotav,</l>
          <l>v&apos;tzivanu l&apos;hadlik</l>
          <l>ner shel Shabbat.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:id="block_D" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F6c4bac16-639d-4efb-80fc-190ead3118e5.jp2/874,2830,2840,527/max/0/default.jpg">
          <l>BLESSED ARE YOU, Adonai our God, Sovereign of the universe,</l>
          <l>who hallows us with mitzvot,</l>
          <l>commanding us to kindle the light of Shabbat.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:id="block_E" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F6c4bac16-639d-4efb-80fc-190ead3118e5.jp2/455,5674,3687,594/max/0/default.jpg">
          <l>Shabbat Candle Blessing - The mitzvah of kindling Shabbat lights in the home is an early rabbinic</l>
          <l>practice (M. Shabbat 2:1ff.) The Shabbat candle blessing is first recorded in the ninth-century</l>
          <l>prayerbook, Seder Rav Amram. Lighting Shabbat candles as part of the synagogue service is an</l>
          <l>innovation of Reform Judaism.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
